subSubSection.paragraph:
The calling song has a dominant frequency between 8.3 and 11.0 kHz, tending to be higher during amplitude modulations. It has a high amplitude plateau spanning approximately 7.6–11.5 kHz (
Fig. 3C
). This plateau broadens during amplitude modulations, extending up to 12.5 kHz (
Fig. 3D
). Males have been observed to be attracted to simulated female wing-flick responses, when these are timed precisely after each echeme (K. Hill and D. Marshall, pers. obs., 
1 December 2006
).

Measurements
(in mm; 
11 males
, 
4 females
). Body length: male 23.9–27.3 (25.8); female 31.3–32.8 (32.2). Fore wing length: male 28.1–32.5 (30.4); female 32.1–35.6 (34.5). Fore wing width: male 9.9–11.7 (10.5); female 11.0–11.9 (11.5). Head width: male 6.5–7.4 (7.0); female 7.58.3 (7.9). Pronotum width: male 7.1–8.1 (7.6); female 8.0–9.3 (8.6). Abdomen width: male 6.6–8.0 (7.4); female 7.18.7 (7.7). Ovipositor length: female 14.3–14.9 (14.7).
